 They're very complicated and beautiful.

41:19.680 --> 41:21.920
 Yeah, but we often oversimplify them.

41:21.920 --> 41:24.800
 Yes, they're actually like there's computation happening

41:24.800 --> 41:25.640
 within a Neuron.

41:25.640 --> 41:29.480
 Right, so I would say to think of a transistor

41:29.480 --> 41:32.320
 as the building block of a digital computer is accurate.

41:32.320 --> 41:34.640
 You use a few transistors to make your logic gates.

41:34.640 --> 41:35.960
 You build up more.

41:35.960 --> 41:37.800
 You build up processors from logic gates

41:37.800 --> 41:39.120
 and things like that.

41:39.120 --> 41:40.560
 So you can think of a transistor

41:40.560 --> 41:42.280
 as a fundamental building block

41:42.280 --> 41:44.520
 or you can think of as we get into more

41:44.520 --> 41:46.320
 highly parallelized architectures,

41:46.320 --> 41:49.280
 you can think of a processor as a fundamental building block

