 And so yes, optical clocks,

56:45.360 --> 56:50.360
 optical clock distribution is a very powerful technology.

56:51.200 --> 56:53.200
 I don't know the state of that field right now,

56:53.200 --> 56:55.640
 but I imagine that if you're trying to distribute a clock

56:55.640 --> 56:59.000
 across any appreciable size computational system,

56:59.000 --> 57:00.360
 you want to use light.

