2:17:24.560 --> 2:17:26.160
 that never sat well with me,

2:17:26.160 --> 2:17:29.480
 but I just kind of moved on because there are things to do

2:17:29.480 --> 2:17:31.200
 and a lot of exciting work,

2:17:31.200 --> 2:17:33.800
 doesn't depend on resolving this puzzle.

2:17:33.800 --> 2:17:38.800
 But as I started working more with technology,

2:17:39.360 --> 2:17:41.840
 getting into the more recent years of my career,

2:17:41.840 --> 2:17:43.760
 particularly when I started,

2:17:43.760 --> 2:17:46.560
 after having worked with silicon for a long time,

2:17:46.560 --> 2:17:49.040
 which was kind of eerie on its own.

2:17:49.040 --> 2:17:51.200
 But then when I switched over to superconductors,

2:17:51.200 --> 2:17:53.600
 I was just like, this is crazy.

2:17:53.600 --> 2:17:57.400
 It's just absolutely astonishing

2:17:57.400 --> 2:18:00.600
 that our universe gives us superconductivity.

2:18:00.600 --> 2:18:02.480
 It's one of the most beautiful physical phenomena,

2:18:02.480 --> 2:18:06.600
 and it's also extraordinarily useful for technology.

2:18:06.600 --> 2:18:08.720
 So you can argue that the universe has to have

2:18:08.720 --> 2:18:11.320
 the parameters it does for us to exist

2:18:11.320 --> 2:18:13.040
 because we couldn't be here otherwise.

2:18:13.040 --> 2:18:14.800
 But why does it give us technology?

2:18:14.800 --> 2:18:18.880
 Why does it give us silicon that has this ideal oxide

2:18:18.880 --> 2:18:20.920
 that allows us to make a transistor

2:18:20.920 --> 2:18:25.120
 without trying that hard, that can't be explained

2:18:25.120 --> 2:18:26.760
 by the same anthropic reasoning?

2:18:27.800 --> 2:18:30.360
 Yeah, so it's asking the why question.

